ZCZC EE30
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
SUNDAY TO WEDNESDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND MARITIME AGENCY
AT 082300 UTC
FM SUNDAY EVENING HIGH PRESSURE WILL REMAIN IN CHARGE ACROSS THE CELTIC
SEA 1034 EXTENDING A LARGE ANTICYCLONIC WIND REGIME ACROSS THE BRITISH
ISLES INDUCING A MOSTLY SETTLED WEATHER PATTERN. THIS HIGH PRESSURE WILL
GRADUALLY RELAX TO 1028 AS IT SLWY MIGRATES S AND E TO BE CENTRED ACROSS
NERN FRANCE BY WEDNESDAY EVENING. THE LOW PRESSURES ACROSS NERN SCANDINAVIA
WILL MAKE SLT PROGRESS AS THEY MOV FURTHER N AND E THROUGH THE PERIOD. A
DEEP LOW PRESSURE WILL REMAIN RELATIVELY IN SITU ACROSS THE CENTRAL/WERN
ATLANTIC THROUGH THE PERIOD BUT THIS WILL SPAWN A DISCRETE LOW PRESSURE
THROUGH TUESDAY AND INTO WEDNESDAY ACROSS ICELAND DPN TO 1001 BY THE END
OF THE PERIOD. AN AREA OF STRG WINDS IS LIKELY TO REMAIN ACROSS FITZROY AND
PERHAPS WERN PARTS OF BISCAY FM SUNDAY WITH A GRADUAL EASING TREND TOWARD
WEDNESDAY
